news.title: More Chinese homebuyers refuse to pay loans amid contagion fears
news.para: Homebuyers have stopped mortgage payments on at least 100 projects in more than 50 cities as of Wednesday, according to researcher China Real Estate Information Corp. That's up from 58 projects on Tuesday and only 28 on Monday, according to Jefferies Financial Group Inc. analysts including Shujin Chen.

news.title: China property protests threaten to dent $220 billion of banks' mortgage loans
news.para: The mortgage bad-loan ratios for banks could rise three- to five-fold as a result of homebuyers stopping mortgage payments, analysts estimate, adding the protests will significantly add to lenders' risk exposure to the cash-starved property sector.

news.title: ACC's net profit down 60% to Rs 227 crore in Apr-Jun 2022
news.para: Total revenue from operations during the quarter under review was Rs 4,468.42 crore as against Rs 3,884.94 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Rising interest rates, inflation to affect affordable housing finance companies' growth: Report
news.para: Affordable housing finance (ticket size below Rs 25 lakh) has proven to be one of the most resilient sectors to economic cycles and seen rapid progress over the past decade, India Ratings and Research said in a report.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board auctions commercial plot in Jaipur for Rs 488 crore
news.para: ​​RHB (Rajasthan Housing Board) commissioner Pawan Arora said that the 45,632-square metre land between VT Road and Aravali Marg in Mansasorver was e-auctioned on Wednesday.

news.title: China banks, property stocks slump as homebuyers stop mortgage payments
news.para: Bonds of Chinese developers were also sold off, as confidence in the sector, already wrecked by the Evergrande Group crisis, continues to wane.

news.title: Gujarat: 90-day penalty waiver for old GHB, SCB schemes
news.para: If the outstanding amount is repaid by the beneficiary within 90 days of implementation of the scheme, there will be a 100 per cent penalty waiver, a release said.

news.title: Don't keep appeals pending for no valid reason, Chandigarh housing board officials told
news.para: As per available information, the CHB has implemented e-services in the month of February and from July 1 acceptance of physical applications has been stopped for those services that have been made available online.

news.title: Colliers appoints Peush Jain as managing director for office services
news.para: "Peush will focus on leasing, tenant representation, portfolio assessment and acquisitions for occupiers," said Ramesh Nair, CEO, India, Colliers

news.title: Kolkata civic body to create 'repair fund' to help heritage building owners in financial distress
news.para: ​Mayor Firhad Hakim on Wednesday said all major corporates that own heritage buildings in Kolkata will have to ensure they are properly maintained.

news.title: Now, defence ministry wants to turn lease land into free-hold
news.para: People who are likely to be affected by the amendment may give their feedback, either by way of suggestions or raising objections, by July 24 (one month from the date of gazette notification issued on June 24).

news.title: Mumbai: 19 residential buildings set to make way for Sewri-Worli connector
news.para: While residents are to be moved to a project-affected people (PAP) tenement at Gomata Nagar, Worli, commercial establishments will be moved into Shirodkar Mandai at J Bhandarkar Marg, Parel.

news.title: Somany Ceramics aims at Rs 2,700 crore turnover this fiscal
news.para: The company's three plants in Haryana, Gujarat and Andhra Pradesh have a total manufacturing capacity of 75 million square metre per annum, including those of the seven subsidiaries and associate facilities, Somany Ceramics Deputy CEO Amit Sahai said.

news.title: Lucknow development body to cancel allotment of 150 houses
news.para: The action was taken after LDA vice-chairperson Indramani Tripathi sanctioned an order based on a complaint that LDA flats and houses are being used for illegal activities.

news.title: Delhi: MCD issues notices to 40,000 residents over property tax
news.para: According to officials, the move is aimed to track those who have not filed property tax for years and also to serve the purpose of updating records.
